 "yield_notes": "High and reliable yields", "growing_notes": "Good disease resistance", "availability": "Australian seed suppliers"}, {"name": "Schooner", "slug": "schooner", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 9, "origin": "Australia", "traits": "Spring barley, malting variety; Suitable for small-scale/home cultivation", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate yields, suitable for backyard growing", "growing_notes": "Standard resistance", "availability": "Seed suppliers, agricultural stores"}, {"name": "Maris Otter", "slug": "maris-otter", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 10, "origin": "United Kingdom, Released 1966", "traits": "Winter barley, two-row, heritage malting variety; Low protein, rich nutty flavor, biscuity character. Highly regarded in brewing for over 55 years", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate by modern standards, but prized for flavor", "growing_notes": "Susceptible to modern diseases, requires fungicide management", "availability": "Specialty malt suppliers, Crisp Malt, Thomas Fawcett, Muntons (primarily as malt)"}, {"name": "Golden Promise", "slug": "golden-promise", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 11, "origin": "Scotland, United Kingdom, Released 1966-1968", "traits": "Spring barley, heritage malting variety; Short, stiff straw, very early maturity (3 weeks before modern varieties), sweet clean flavor. First variety protected under UK Plant Varieties Act 1964", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Lower than modern varieties, but flavor-focused", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Chevallier", "slug": "chevallier", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 12, "origin": "England, United Kingdom, 1820s-1920s", "traits": "Landrace heritage barley, first modern malting variety; Ancestral to modern malting varieties. Nutty, bready, marmalade fla